---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Our Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'leaving-denmark', text: 'Leaving Danish Healthcare', level: 2 },
  { id: 'tax-considerations', text: 'Tax Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Quick Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'popular-destinations', text: 'Popular Destinations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Best Europe Insurance', href: '/best/europe-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best US Coverage Insurance', href: '/best/us-coverage-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best UK Expat Insurance', href: '/best/uk-expat-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'euNetwork', header: 'EU Network' },
  { key: 'globalNetwork', header: 'Global Network' },
  { key: 'denmarkCoverage', header: 'Denmark Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Starting Price' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', euNetwork: 'Excellent', globalNetwork: 'Excellent', denmarkCoverage: 'Add-on', price: 'DKK 1,400/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', euNetwork: 'Excellent', globalNetwork: 'Excellent', denmarkCoverage: 'Add-on', price: 'DKK 1,600/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', euNetwork: 'Excellent', globalNetwork: 'Strong', denmarkCoverage: 'Add-on', price: 'DKK 1,350/mo' },
  { provider: 'Tryg', euNetwork: 'Good', globalNetwork: 'Limited', denmarkCoverage: 'Included', price: 'DKK 1,100/mo' },
  { provider: 'Codan Forsikring', euNetwork: 'Good', globalNetwork: 'Limited', denmarkCoverage: 'Included', price: 'DKK 1,000/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Health Insurance for Danish Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for Danish expats. Find coverage for the US, UK, and other destinations while understanding your Danish healthcare options."
  headline="Best Insurance for Danish Expats in 2026"
  subheadline="Denmark's healthcare is excellent, but it doesn't follow you abroad. Here's how to stay covered when you work or live outside Denmark."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/pages/danish-expat-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Cigna Quote →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Our Top Picks</h2>
  <p>
    Danish expats work globally—from US tech companies to international organizations across Europe and beyond. Understanding how leaving Denmark affects your healthcare coverage is important. Here's what we recommend:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Best overall for Danish expats. Excellent global networks, comprehensive coverage matching Danish quality expectations.</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa Global:</strong> Premium option with top-tier service quality. Outstanding worldwide networks.</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Strong European coverage at competitive prices. Good value for EU-based expats.</li>
    <li><strong>Tryg:</strong> Major Danish insurer with international products. Familiar brand, Denmark coverage included.</li>
    <li><strong>Codan Forsikring:</strong> Danish insurer offering international coverage. Familiar service for Danish nationals.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Quality Expectations"
    description="Danish healthcare is world-class. Don't accept inferior coverage abroad—international insurance should match the quality you're accustomed to in Denmark."
    buttonText="Get Quality Coverage Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="leaving-denmark">Leaving Danish Healthcare</h2>
  <p>
    Denmark's healthcare system is tax-funded and excellent. Here's what happens when you leave:
  </p>

  <h3>Sundhedsstyrelsen (Danish Health Authority)</h3>
  <p>
    Danish healthcare is provided through the regions (regioner) and funded by taxes. When you leave Denmark and are no longer a Danish tax resident, you lose access to the Danish healthcare system.
  </p>

  <h3>Yellow Health Card (Sundhedskort)</h3>
  <p>
    Your yellow health card is tied to Danish residence. When you move abroad, you must de-register (folkeregistret) and surrender your card. You lose access to Danish GP services and hospital care.
  </p>

  <h3>EU Healthcare Coordination</h3>
  <p>
    If you move within the EU/EEA, social security coordination rules apply. You may access healthcare in your new country of residence. The S1 form (for posted workers or pensioners) allows continued Danish healthcare responsibility in some cases.
  </p>

  <h3>Private Danish Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Private health insurance from Danish companies (Tryg, Codan, Topdanmark) typically provides limited international coverage. For comprehensive protection abroad, international insurance is necessary.
  </p>

  <h2 id="tax-considerations">Tax Considerations</h2>
  <p>
    Danish tax rules have implications for expats:
  </p>

  <h3>Tax Residency</h3>
  <p>
    When you leave Denmark and establish residence elsewhere, you typically cease being a Danish tax resident. This affects your healthcare access since Danish healthcare is tax-funded.
  </p>

  <h3>Double Taxation Agreements</h3>
  <p>
    Denmark has double taxation agreements with many countries. Your tax situation depends on your destination and employment status. Healthcare is separate from tax but linked through residency.
  </p>

  <h3>Pension and Healthcare</h3>
  <p>
    Danish state pension (folkepension) can be paid abroad. Healthcare access depends on residence, not pension receipt. Pensioners in EU countries may use an S1 form for healthcare coordination.
  </p>

  <h3>Returning to Denmark</h3>
  <p>
    When you return and re-register, you regain access to Danish healthcare. There may be a brief administrative period before your yellow card is issued.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">EU Blue Card and Posted Workers</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      If you're posted abroad by a Danish employer or hold an EU Blue Card, special rules may apply. Your employer may maintain Danish social security contributions, affecting your healthcare situation.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Quick Comparison</h2>
  <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers comprehensive international coverage matching Danish quality expectations. Strong networks worldwide, including US (important for many Danish professionals). Plans come in three tiers with coverage up to unlimited.
  </p>

  <p>
    24/7 service with excellent response times. Denmark coverage can be added for visits home.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Danish expats who want quality coverage matching Danish standards worldwide.
  </p>

  <h3>Bupa Global</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers premium international coverage with excellent worldwide networks. Service quality is outstanding—matching Danish efficiency expectations. Top-tier option for those who want the best.
  </p>

  <p>
    Higher pricing reflects premium quality. Denmark coverage available as an add-on.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Danish professionals who want top-tier coverage and service quality.
  </p>

  <h3>Allianz Care</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers excellent European coverage at competitive prices. Strong networks throughout the EU—valuable for Danish expats in European countries. Good value for comprehensive coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Danish expats in EU countries who want strong European networks at good value.
  </p>

  <h3>Tryg</h3>
  <p>
    Tryg is one of Denmark's largest insurers and offers international products. Familiar brand, Danish service, Denmark coverage included automatically. International networks are adequate for most destinations.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Danish expats who prefer familiar Danish service with seamless home coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Codan Forsikring</h3>
  <p>
    Codan is a major Danish insurer offering international coverage options. Familiar service, Denmark coverage included. Networks adequate for common Danish expat destinations.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Danish expats who want familiar service and integrated Denmark coverage.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Quality Options"
    description="Danish expats expect quality. Compare top-tier plans that match your standards for your specific destination."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
  />

  <h2 id="popular-destinations">Popular Destinations</h2>
  <p>
    Danish expats have specific destination patterns:
  </p>

  <h3>United States</h3>
  <p>
    Popular for professionals, especially in tech and pharma. US healthcare is extremely expensive—comprehensive coverage is essential. No public healthcare access for non-residents.
  </p>

  <h3>United Kingdom</h3>
  <p>
    Common destination for professionals. NHS provides healthcare to legal residents. Post-Brexit, EU coordination rules no longer apply. Private insurance supplements NHS for faster access.
  </p>

  <h3>Germany</h3>
  <p>
    Close neighbor with strong business connections. German statutory insurance (GKV) covers employees. Private insurance provides additional options and coverage for self-employed.
  </p>

  <h3>Sweden and Norway</h3>
  <p>
    Nordic neighbors with similar healthcare systems. Nordic Convention provides some coordination for short-term stays. Long-term residence requires registration in the local system.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Does Danish healthcare cover me abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Danish healthcare covers emergency treatment in EU countries via the blue EU health card. Living abroad long-term requires either local coverage or international insurance.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What happens to my yellow card?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">When you de-register from Denmark (CPR), you surrender your yellow health card. You regain access when you return and re-register.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Can I keep Danish coverage if posted abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Posted workers may maintain Danish social security through an A1 certificate. This keeps Danish healthcare responsibility for a limited period. Check rules with your employer.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about coverage during Denmark visits?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Tryg and Codan include Denmark automatically. International insurers offer Denmark as a coverage region. Without insurance, you'd pay private rates during visits.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Tryg or Cigna better?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Tryg offers Danish familiarity and includes Denmark. Cigna has stronger global networks. Choose based on destination and how important Danish service integration is.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about Nordic countries?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Nordic Convention provides some coordination, but living in another Nordic country requires registration in that country's system. International insurance provides flexibility.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Danish expats need comprehensive international insurance—Danish healthcare doesn't follow you abroad. <strong>Cigna Global</strong> and <strong>Bupa Global</strong> match Danish quality expectations with excellent global networks.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Allianz Care</strong> offers good value for EU destinations. <strong>Tryg</strong> and <strong>Codan</strong> suit those who prefer familiar Danish service with included home coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    Remember: Danish healthcare is tied to Danish tax residency. Plan your healthcare transition when planning your move abroad.
  </p>

</PageShell>
